Medford City Council, Committee of the Whole, meeting notice, Wednesday, October 5th, 2022 at 6 p.m. on paper 22-496. Mr. Clerk, please call the roll. Councilor Kerrio-Lewis, it's going to be late. Councilor Collins. Present. Councilor Knight. Councilor Scarpelli, I see. Present. Councilor Hussain. Present.

2
00:00:32,077 --> 00:00:45,273
Vice President Beers. Present. Five present, two absent. The meeting is called to order. There'll be a meeting of the Medford City Council Committee of the Whole on Wednesday, October 5th, 2022 at 6 p.m. in the Medford City Council Chamber on the second floor of Medford City Hall.

3
00:00:46,370 --> 00:01:12,863
The purpose of this meeting is to discuss the draft Medford Comprehensive Plan, paper 22-496. The council has invited Director of Planning, Development and Sustainability, Alicia Hunt, staff members from the Office of Planning, Development and Sustainability, and members of the Comprehensive Plan Consultants Team. For further information, aids and accommodations, contact the City Clerk at 781-393-2425. Sincerely yours, Nicole Morrell, Council President. Thank you for being here today.

4
00:01:13,420 --> 00:01:41,517
As I just said, we're here to talk about the draft Medford Comprehensive Plan. We have a number of folks both in the room and on Zoom who have worked diligently on the plan and are going to present kind of an overview to us. Then we will turn it over to the counselors for questions, perhaps members of the public. And then after that, we'd love to hear what the next steps are since this is a draft and it will be going into a finalization state.

5
00:01:42,074 --> 00:02:01,835
With that, unless there are immediate questions from the council, I will turn it over to Director Hunt. Good evening, Councillors. Thank you for having us this evening. The Medford Comprehensive Plan has been a work in progress for almost the past 18 months.

